OL,3,CChange rules to allow public sector
OL,4,Cinvestment borrowing, Swinney to tell
OL,5,CReeves
OL,7,FHe is expected to rail against
OL,8,Fexpected cuts by Chancellor Rachel
OL,9,FReeves in the Budget, instead urging
OL,10,Fher to boost public investment.
OL,12,FOne of the changes, the First Minister
OL,13,Fis expected to say, should be movement
OL,14,Fon fiscal rules which would allow
OL,15,Finvestment in public infrastructure.
OL,17,FThe current rules place a cap on
OL,18,Fpublic sector borrowing of 3%.
