OL,5,CReeves
OL,7,F"Labour productivity grew by just 0.4%
OL,8,Fa year in the UK in the 12 years
OL,9,Ffollowing the financial crisis, half
OL,10,Fthe rate of the 25 richest OECD
OL,11,Fcountries.
OL,13,F"And it means ` as the Resolution
OL,14,FFoundation have found ` almost a
OL,15,Fdecade and a half of lost earnings. It
OL,16,Fwas only in 2023 that real wages were
OL,17,Fback to where they were before the
OL,18,Ffinancial crisis. 15 years of lost
OL,19,Fwage growth has cost the average
OL,20,Fworker #10,700 a year.
